A statistical model is termed [nonparametric](/Nonparametric_model) if the parameter set



Θ


{\displaystyle \Theta }

has infinite dimension. A [semiparametric](/Semiparametric_model) model is one that incorporates both finite-dimensional and infinite-dimensional parameters. Formally, if k represents the dimension of



Θ


